#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 19. Satthāravandanāsutta → dutiyasakkanamassanasuttaṃ (bj, s2, s3) | sakkanamassanasuttaṃ (2) (s1) | sakka-namassana (2) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Satthāravandanāsutta "
msgstr "19. Who Sakka Worships "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.235, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ jetavane. "
msgstr "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali, "

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.3"
msgid "‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmiṃ dassanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā sakkassa devānamindassa paṭivedesi: "
msgstr "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka, "

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.5"
msgid "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho. "
msgstr "‘Good sir, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been harnessed. "

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.6"
msgid "Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti. "
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṃ katvā sudaṃ bhagavantaṃ namassati. "
msgstr "Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, and revered the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "So Mātali the charioteer addressed Sakka in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.1"
msgid "‘Yañhi devā manussā ca, "
msgstr "‘Gods and men "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.2"
msgid "taṃ namassanti vāsava; "
msgstr "worship you, Vāsava. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.3"
msgid "Atha ko nāma so yakkho, "
msgstr "So what’s the name of the spirit "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.4"
msgid "yaṃ tvaṃ sakka namassasī’ti. "
msgstr "that you worship, Sakka?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.505, sc3
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.1"
msgid "‘Yo idha sammāsambuddho, "
msgstr "‘It’s the fully awakened Buddha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.2"
msgid "asmiṃ loke sadevake; "
msgstr "the Teacher of peerless name "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.3"
msgid "Anomanāmaṃ satthāraṃ, "
msgstr "in this world with its gods—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.4"
msgid "taṃ namassāmi mātali. "
msgstr "that’s who I worship, Mātali. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.1"
msgid "Yesaṃ rāgo ca doso ca, "
msgstr "Those who have discarded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.2"
msgid "avijjā ca virājitā; "
msgstr "greed, hate, and ignorance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.3"
msgid "Khīṇāsavā arahanto, "
msgstr "the perfected ones with defilements ended—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.4"
msgid "te namassāmi mātali. "
msgstr "they're who I worship, Mātali. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.1"
msgid "Ye rāgadosavinayā, "
msgstr "The trainees who take pleasure in decreasing suffering, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.2"
msgid "avijjāsamatikkamā; "
msgstr "diligently pursuing the training "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on this. Given that the verse has five padas, it’s almost certain that there is textual corruption. Treating these as truncated datives is a kludge, but I can’t think of a better alternative.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.3"
msgid "Sekkhā apacayārāmā, "
msgstr "for getting rid of greed and hate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.4"
msgid "appamattānusikkhare; "
msgstr "and going past ignorance—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.5"
msgid "Te namassāmi mātalī’ti. "
msgstr "they’re who I worship, Mātali.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.1"
msgid "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Those who you worship "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.2"
msgid "ye tvaṃ sakka namassasi; "
msgstr "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.3"
msgid "Ahampi te namassāmi, "
msgstr "I too will worship "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.4"
msgid "ye namassasi vāsavā’ti. "
msgstr "those who you worship, Sakka.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.1"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna maghavā, "
msgstr "After saying this, Maghavā the chief, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.2"
msgid "devarājā sujampati; "
msgstr "king of gods, Sujā’s husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.3"
msgid "Bhagavantaṃ namassitvā, "
msgstr "having worshipped the Buddha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.4"
msgid "pamukho rathamāruhī”ti. "
msgstr "climbed into his chariot.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
